'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFSCTL 1 "2026-03-04" "kafs 0.2.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kafsctl \- query runtime stats from a mounted kafs filesystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafsctl
.B stats
.I mountpoint
.RB [ --json ]
.PP
.B kafsctl
.B migrate
.I image
.RB [ --yes ]
.PP
.B kafsctl
.B hotplug
.I subcommand
.I mountpoint
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafsctl
queries a running
.BR kafs (1)
instance for filesystem/HRL statistics via FUSE ioctl, and sends hotplug control requests
via the hidden control endpoint
.IR /.kafs.sock .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B stats
Print current stats for the mounted filesystem at
.IR mountpoint .
Use
.B --json
to emit machine-readable JSON.
.TP
.B migrate
Migrate an offline v2 image to v3.
This operation is irreversible.
Without
.BR --yes ,
interactive confirmation is required.
.TP
.B hotplug status
Show hotplug status, including session/epoch and compatibility.
.TP
.B hotplug restart-back
Request a hotplug reconnect and back process restart.
The mounted
.B kafs
front spawns
.B kafs-back
by default, or
.B KAFS_HOTPLUG_BACK_BIN
when configured via hotplug env.
.TP
.B hotplug compat
Show front/back version compatibility.
.TP
.B hotplug set-timeout
Set the reconnect wait timeout (milliseconds).
.TP
.B hotplug env list|set|unset
Manage environment variables passed to the back process on restart.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
